I received a first-class (top) B.Sc. honors degree in Computer
Systems Engineering from University of Kent and a Ph.D. degree in Computer Science from 
University of Cambridge. I have been on the faculty of Durham University, City
University of Hong Kong, and The Hong Kong Polytechnic University. I am an
    Honorary Professor at Swansea University, United Kingdom.

<p>My research interests include computer graphics, computer vision, and the
  development of deep-learning techniques for solving computer graphics/vision
  problems. The papers from my group appear in SIGGRAPH, SIGGRAPH Asia, CVPR,
  ICCV, ECCV, AAAI and NeurIPS. We also 
have papers in TVCG, IJCV, TPAMI, and TIP.  Refer to my <a
href="http://www.cs.cityu.edu.hk/~rynson/publications.html">publications</a> for
more information. I received an Adobe Research Gift in 2023.

<P>I serve on the Editorial Board of <I><a
href="https://www.springer.com/journal/11263/">International Journal of
      Computer Vision (IJCV)</a></i>. I am glad to receive the <i>Springer Nature
    Editorial Contribution Award 2025</i> for my contributions to IJCV.
  I am also serving as the SPC of <i><a href="https://aaai.org/conference/aaai-26/">AAAI 2026</a></i>.
  
  

<p>I served as the Guest Editor of a number of journal 
special issues, including <I><A href="http://www.acm.org/toit/">ACM Trans. on 
Internet Technology</A></I>, <I><A 
href="http://www.ieee.org/organizations/society/sp/tmm/">IEEE Trans. on 
Multimedia</A></I>, <I><A href="http://www.computer.org/tvcg/">IEEE Trans. on 
Visualization and Computer Graphics</A></I>, and <I><A 
href="http://www.computer.org/cga/">IEEE Computer Graphics &amp; 
Applications</A></I>. In addition, I also served on the committees of a number of conferences, including 
Program Co-Chair of <I><A 
href="http://www.cs.cityu.edu.hk/~vrst2004/">ACM VRST 2004</A></I> (Hong Kong), 
